                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.73/20: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bundy</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-02-08T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 8, 1919, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Legation[’s] February 4, 11 a.m.</p>
                <p>Department would be willing to recommend for appointment by Liberian Government
                    technical expert to supervise plant and staff in case Liberia becomes solely
                    dependent upon German wireless plant for communication.</p>
                <p>The American Mission at Paris has been advised of each step in the German cable
                    controversy with request to keep the Liberian Mission advised.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
